  "overview_metadata": {
    "overview_number": 3,
    "overview_title": "Jack and Jill Went Up the Hill",
    "overview_subtitle": "Using Similar Triangles to Understand the Steepness of a Line",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students derive the equation for a proportional linear relationship, <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi></math>. They use similar right triangles to explain why the steepness and direction (slope) of any line is the same between any two distinct points on a non-vertical line."
  },
